    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/dr-cou1-cpb-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The 6 non-assessed factors are consistent with MRL 2 expectations per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. Validation results for pressure head and NIH demonstrate adequate agreement with experimental data. The relative haemolysis index RH < 1 criterion is satisfied at all tested operating points. The assessment team notes that cycle-to-cycle flow variability in the PIV validation result was evaluated qualitatively rather than through a structured UQ process; this is considered acceptable given the supporting quantitative UQ on the primary haemolysis QoI. The overall evidence package supports an Accepted decision for the CPB COU at Medium assurance level.",
